Almost all values are ratios expressed as percentages. For example, to compute the data item or variable M10 "Percent Hispanic" the numerator is the number of persons of Hispanic origin in the block group. The denominator is the total population of the block group. Some numerators or denominators involve aggregates of finer Census data. For example, we must add together 13 age categories to obtain M1, a total for ages 0-18. M1. Percent of Population Age 0 to 18 M2. Percent of Population Age 0 to 5 M3.
